Tic Tac Toe — Enhanced (HTML/CSS/JS)

Features
- Animated placement of X/O with graceful transitions
- Shield power-up (protects a chosen empty cell once)
- Slow Time power-up (delays opponent's next move)
- Play vs AI (Minimax) or 2-player local mode
- Optional sprite-sheet visuals (sprites.png) for richer appearance
- Responsive UI and keyboard shortcuts
- Restart & lightweight accessibility hooks

How to run
1. Put files in a folder: index.html, style.css, script.js
2. Optionally add sprites.png for custom visuals (see sprite spec below)
3. Open index.html in any modern browser (Chrome/Firefox/Edge)
4. For hosting, push to GitHub and enable GitHub Pages (or drag to Netlify)

Sprite sheet (optional)
- Name file: sprites.png
- Arrange frames horizontally: [X-frame][O-frame][extra]
- Each frame should be same width — e.g., 300x100 each — total width 900x100 if 3 frames
- The CSS will set background-position automatically for basic two-frame usage

Resume blurb (1–2 lines)
- "Built an enhanced Tic Tac Toe web game (HTML/CSS/vanilla JS) with Minimax AI, animated visuals, and power-ups (Shield & Slow Time). Implemented responsive UI and optional sprite-sheet graphics."

